---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title={"Built-in Ad and Tracker Blocking Browser | Blanc"}
  description={"Blanc includes ad and tracker blocking in the browser, with a live shield count and a per-site option when you want to allow ads."}
  path="/features/ad-blocking"
  page="feature-ad-blocking"
  current="features"
  ogDescription={"Built-in ad and tracker blocking with a quiet shield count and a per-site option when you want to allow ads."}
  ogImage="/feature-ad-blocking.png"
  ogImageAlt={"Blanc's floating Island over a web page, with the blocking shield visible."}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline slot="head">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://blancbrowser.com/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Features", "item": "https://blancbrowser.com/features" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Built-in ad and tracker blocking", "item": "https://blancbrowser.com/features/ad-blocking" }
  ]
}
</script>

<main class="feature-page feature-detail-page">
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">home</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><a href="/features">features</a><span aria-hidden="true">/</span><span aria-current="page">ad blocking</span></nav>
  <section class="feature-hero feature-hero--detail" aria-labelledby="blocking-title">
    <p class="section-kicker">built in</p>
    <h1 id="blocking-title">Fewer ads. Less tracking. No extension required.</h1>
    <p>Blanc uses built-in blocking lists to stop ads and known trackers at the browser level. The shield on the Island shows what was blocked on the page.</p>
  </section>

  <figure class="product-capture feature-capture">
    <div class="demo-stage island-figure" data-page-tone="netflix" role="img" aria-label="Blanc's floating Island over the Netflix website, showing the current domain netflix.com next to a shield count of three blocked items.">
      <div class="demo-page" aria-hidden="true"><div class="bar w1"></div><div class="bar w2"></div><div class="bar w3"></div><div class="bar w4"></div></div>
      <picture>
        <source media="(max-width: 560px)" srcset="/shots/mobile/netflix.jpg">
        <img class="demo-shot show" src="/shots/desktop/netflix.jpg" loading="lazy" alt="" aria-hidden="true">
      </picture>
      <div class="demo-island" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="pill">
          <div class="pnav">
            <span class="pbtn"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M9.75 3.5 5.25 8l4.5 4.5"/></svg></span>
            <span class="pbtn off"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M6.25 3.5 10.75 8l-4.5 4.5"/></svg></span>
          </div>
          <div class="dots"><span></span><span class="cur"></span><span></span><span></span></div>
          <span class="pill-fav" style="background-image:url('/favicons/netflix.com.ico')"></span>
          <span class="domain">netflix.com</span>
          <span class="shield">3</span>
          <span class="psep"></span>
          <div class="pacts">
            <span class="pbtn"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M12.42 10.35a5 5 0 1 1-4.42-7.35c1.4 0 2.74.56 3.74 1.53L13 5.78"/><path d="M13 3v2.78h-2.78"/></svg></span>
            <span class="pbtn heart"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M8 13.25C4.6 11 2.75 8.9 2.75 6.6a2.85 2.85 0 0 1 5.25-1.54A2.85 2.85 0 0 1 13.25 6.6c0 2.3-1.85 4.4-5.25 6.65z"/></svg></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <figcaption>The shield sits alongside the site you are visiting, so the status stays clear without becoming a dashboard.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <section class="feature-copy-grid" aria-labelledby="built-in-title">
    <div>
      <p class="section-kicker">the blocker is part of the browser</p>
      <h2 id="built-in-title">Start protected, not set up.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-copy-list">
      <article>
        <h3>Built around the web, not a browser store.</h3>
        <p>Blanc loads ad and tracker block lists directly in the browser. You do not need to find, install, or manage an extension before browsing.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>A quiet count when it matters.</h3>
        <p>The shield on the Island displays the number of blocked items for the current page. It is there as a useful signal, not a second dashboard to manage.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Let a site through when you choose.</h3>
        <p>Need a site exception? Open the Island and type <code>/allow-ads</code>. Blanc keeps the choice specific to that site instead of making it an all-or-nothing setting.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <aside class="truth-note" aria-labelledby="truth-note-title">
    <p class="section-kicker">good to know</p>
    <h2 id="truth-note-title">Blocking is a strong default, not a guarantee.</h2>
    <p>Blanc uses EasyList and EasyPrivacy to reduce ads and known tracking. No blocker can promise to remove every advertisement or tracker, and some sites may need an exception to work as intended.</p>
    <a class="text-link" href="/privacy#browsing-the-web-with-blanc">Read Blanc's network and privacy details <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
  </aside>

  <section class="feature-close" aria-labelledby="blocking-close-title">
    <p class="section-kicker">built into every download</p>
    <h2 id="blocking-close-title">Browse with less following you around.</h2>
    <a class="cta" href="/download" data-track="feature_cta_click" data-feature="ad-blocking" data-cta-position="feature-close">download blanc</a>
  </section>
</main>
</BaseLayout>
